T*
(Feedback and Bias) Tj
T*
(------------------------------------------------------------) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(In RTB, feedback is censored. The system observes clicks or conversions only for ads that) Tj
T*
(were selected, bid on, won, and rendered. Therefore, naive training on won impressions can) Tj
T*
(learn the behavior of the auction and pacing system rather than intrinsic ad relevance.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(A production-quality log should contain:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(* request id, context, timestamp, user/session privacy-safe keys;) Tj
T*
(* all eligible ads before filtering;) Tj
T*
(* selected top-K set, scores, and propensities;) Tj
T*
(* bid decision, bid price, pacing multiplier, and shading multiplier;) Tj
T*
(* win/loss, clearing price when available, impression, click, conversion, and delayed) Tj
T*
(labels;) Tj
T*
(* model version, feature version, and exploration parameters.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(For offline evaluation, use randomized exploration traffic and estimators such as inverse) Tj
T*
(propensity scoring \(IPS\), self-normalized IPS, or doubly robust estimators. Deterministic) Tj
T*
(logs from a greedy policy are insufficient for unbiased evaluation of alternative policies.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
