(Disjoint LinUCB) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Classical disjoint LinUCB maintains independent parameters per arm. For arm a:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(A_a | = I + _s:a_s=a x_s x_s^, |) Tj
T*
(b_a | = _s:a_s=a r_s x_s, |) Tj
T*
(_a | = A_a^-1b_a.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The score is) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(p_t\(a\)=_a^ x_t\(a\)+x_t\(a\)^ A_a^-1x_t\(a\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(It is easy to implement and interpretable, but pure per-arm learning is weak for new ads) Tj
T*
(because a newly introduced arm has no history.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Feature-Based Shared LinUCB) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(A practical first step is to represent ads by features and learn one shared model:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(A | = I + _s x_s x_s^, |) Tj
T*
(b | = _s r_s x_s, |) Tj
T*
(| = A^-1b,) Tj
T*
(p_t\(a\) | =^ x_t\(a\)+x_t\(a\)^ A^-1x_t\(a\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This transfers learning across ads through metadata and interactions, so it is better for) Tj
T*
(cold start. It should be the first reliable baseline for this repository.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Hybrid LinUCB) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Hybrid LinUCB decomposes the reward into a global component and an arm-specific component:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(z_t\(a\)^ + x_t\(a\)^_a.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Here z_t\(a\) captures common features shared across arms, while x_t\(a\) captures arm-local) Tj
